[The figures provided by Dr. Brian Gushulak change the perception of the
Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) situation in Southern Europe. It is
clear that CCHF virus is present in this region and that there is potential
for spread beyond this region. Health professionals should be aware that
travellers in and out of this region may be exposed to and have contracted
infection where there is evidence of contact with ticks. - Mod.CP
